4.  Faction types

	Each player must choose a faction type:

		dwarves elves men . . .  orcs sea kings savages undead

	Recruit is always of same type

	Faction type limits skills which can be learned

	Common:
		Combat
		Construction
		Shipcraft
		Stealth
		Religion
		Basic magic

	Dwarves:
		Mining
		Gatecraft

	Elves:
		Forestry
		Shipcraft
		Scrying (Elven magic)
		access to Faerie

	Men:
		Alchemy
		Persuasion
		Shipcraft
		TRAIN order

	Savages:
		Beastmastery
		Weather magic

	Undead:
		Necromancy
		access to Hades

	Different NP allotments to balance?
	Also choose either Good or Evil.


	Good:
		advanced meditation

	Evil:
		fear loyalty
		torture
		raise orc unit

	Orcs:
		Beastmastery

	Sea Kings:
		Shipcraft


Kingdoms/groups


	found
		kingdom/group
		declared enemy
		land acquisition goal
		structures owned/dedicated goal
		membership goal


Groups are defined by:

	faction		player's entire faction must join
			the faction may not belong to another
			exclusive group

	individual	characters may join these groups.  the faction
			may be part of a faction group.  A character
			may only join one individual group

	non-exclusive	characters or factions may join, no restrictions.


	skills		skills the faction provides which members may study


	land		members claim land in the name of the group
			all existing owned land becomes group territory



The legend of the Crown, Scepter and Chalice
--------------------------------------------

The three artifacts have been lost.  Nasty monsters are guarding them.
A king must take all three to mount Zukko in Torba Bacor, and there
peform the sacred ritual (issue the USE command for one of the artifact).

The ritual will claim the Emperorship for the king, and give him vast
powers.

Which are:
	build citadel skill ?
	raise imperial guard units
	imperial income based



1.  GARRISON <kind> <number> [...]

	Install a garrision of men in the location.
	Must be the first unit in the location.
	Cannot be used if there is already a garrison.

	    Garrison [3465], lord Feasel the Great [2311], with 10 soldiers

	Garrison is by default on guard.
	Garrison's attitudes with respect to HOSTILE and DEFEND
	are those of the unit which created it.

	UNGARRISON [who] command.

1a. Initially garrison unpopulated provinces?  Default hostile?

	Garrison [3465], with 10 savages


2.  Each garrisoned province provides 100 gold to offset maint costs.
    Remainder is forwarded to the owner.

3.  Number of provinces garrisoned determine's the owner's status:

	lord		1-3
	baron		4-8
	count		9-13
	earl		14-19
	marquess	20-25
	duke		26+

	king	whole region

=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

If owner belongs to a group, province is declared to be part of the
group too.

10% of each garrison's money goes to the group

Raise unit from each group-owned province.

Garrisons DEFEND members of group

